{"word":"ὀρσοθύρη","slug":"ὀρσοθύρη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n75368\" key=\"o)rsoqu/rh\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὀρσο-θύρη</orth> <pron extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pron\">[ῠ]</pron>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen>, prob. <sense id=\"n75368.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">a door high up in the wall,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:22:126\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.126</biblScope></bibl>,<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:333\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">333</biblScope> </bibl> ; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀν᾽ ὀρσοθύρην ἀναβαίη</foreign> ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:132\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">132</biblScope> </bibl> : sens. obsc., <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">τῆς ὄπισθεν ὀ.</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0260.tlg001:17\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Semon.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">17</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> [where <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">υ</itype> appears to be long]. (<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">θύρα ἐν ὕψει τοῦ τοίχου,</foreign> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Phot.</author></bibl>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Suid.</author></bibl>, cf. the second explanation in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author> </bibl>: a form <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀρσορόκα</foreign> (acc. sg.) given by <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Apollod.</author> </bibl> ap. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4099.tlg001:633:57\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ EM\">EM</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">633.57</biblScope> </bibl> sqq. is apptly. corrupt:— <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀρσοθύρη</foreign> was derived in antiquity from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀρούω,</foreign> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ EM\">EM</a></title_> l. c., etc.: the true etym. is uncertain, but cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὄρρος, ὀρρόβηλος.</foreign>)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}